definition.value: An oligopeptide with an N-terminal L-tryptohan residue; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of N-acetyl-L-methionine and N-acetyl-D-methionine.
A hexitol that is hexane-1,2,3,4,5,6-hexol having (2S,3S,4R,5S) configuration; the L-enantiomer of altritol.
A dimethoxyflavone that is scutellarein in which the hydroxy groups at positions 4' and 7 are replaced by methoxy groups. It is an effective anti-HCV agent.
A trimethoxyflavone that is scutellarein in which the hydroxy groups at positions 4', 6, and 7 are replaced by methoxy groups.

A potent cell-permeable and bivalent Smac mimetic which binds to XIAP, cIAP-1 and cIAP-2 proteins (Ki = 0.56 nM,  0.31 nM and 1.1 nM, respectively). It induces apoptosis and tumor regression in cancer xenograft models.
A mixture containing nirmatrelvir and ritonavir. It is co-administered in tablet form for the treatment and post-exposure prophylaxis of COVID-19.
